<p>
&appName; is a set of four programs for inferring the
set of elements affected by a perturbation of a biological
system, based on multiple types of evidence.  &appName; is written
in Java, and is based on the
<a href="&webBaseURL;/&localJavaLibraryName;">&localJavaLibraryName;
library</a>.  The software is available for download within a 
<a href="&appVersion;/&installerDownloadRelURL;">self-extracting
installer</a>.  It is distributed under the <a
href="../License.html">GNU Lesser General Public License</a> (LGPL),
which is a standard &quot;free software&quot; and &quot;open
source&quot; license.  &appName; requires the Java 2 Runtime
Environment (JRE) version 1.4 or newer, or an equivalent JRE.  For
more information about the &appName; system, please consult the 
<a href="docs/UserManual.html">&appName; User Manual</a>.
</p>
